1
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:26,860
<i>( typewriter keys</i>
<i>clicking slowly )</i>

2
00:00:30,196 --> 00:00:32,282
<i>( typewriter dings )</i>

3
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,129
SHIT, MAN.
YOU SCARED THE HELL
OUT OF ME.

4
00:01:28,129 --> 00:01:30,673
TAKE IT.

5
00:01:33,551 --> 00:01:35,887
I HAVEN'T GOT TIME
TO PLAY WITH YOU, PHIL.

6
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:37,764
YOU SEE ALL THAT WORK
I GOT?

7
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:39,599
YOU'RE BACK ON.

8
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:41,601
WHAT?

9
00:01:41,601 --> 00:01:44,646
IT WASN'T EASY.
JENNINGS FOUGHT ME
EVERY INCH OF THE WAY,

10
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:47,690
BUT YOU'RE BACK ON.

11
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:49,692
MAYBE HE'S RIGHT, MAN.

12
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:52,070
NO, HE'S NOT.
NEVER WAS,

13
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:54,697
NOT ABOUT ANY OF THAT SHIT
THEY TALK ABOUT YOU.

14
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:56,866
I'M COOL.
I LIKE IT DOWN HERE.

15
00:01:56,866 --> 00:01:58,868
( laughs )

16
00:01:58,868 --> 00:02:00,495
RIGHT.

17
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:02,997
<i>WE NEED YOU, PARTNER.</i>

18
00:02:02,997 --> 00:02:06,459
YOU KNOW THE O.C. PLAYERS
BETTER THAN ANYBODY.

19
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:12,632
YOU'RE BACK ON, JACK.

20
00:02:12,632 --> 00:02:14,717
<i>( distant siren wailing )</i>

21
00:02:35,029 --> 00:02:36,656
I OWE YOU, MAN.

22
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:39,242
YOU DON'T OWE ME
ANYTHING.

23
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:46,040
<i>( siren wailing )</i>

24
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,239
<i>( crash )</i>

25
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,241
<i>TONY.</i>
- YEAH?

26
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:04,827
<i>DID I EVER TELL YOU</i>
<i>ABOUT THE TIME I WAS</i>
<i>IN BOARDING SCHOOL?</i>

27
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:06,829
NAH, YOU DIDN'T.

28
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:09,040
<i>IT WAS DURING NAP TIME.</i>

29
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:14,504
OH, BABY.

30
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:17,006
IT WAS SO HOT,

31
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:19,467
I'VE DOZED OFF.

32
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:21,886
OH, YEAH.

33
00:04:21,886 --> 00:04:23,721
YOU KNOW
HOW I DOZED OFF?

34
00:04:23,721 --> 00:04:25,014
HOW?

35
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:27,016
I WAS NAKED
UNDER THE SHEETS.

36
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:28,685
OH, YEAH?

37
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,020
THAT'S THE WAY I LIKE YOU.
WHAT HAPPENED?

38
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:32,814
WELL, THEN

39
00:04:32,814 --> 00:04:35,608
MY LITTLE HAND
DROPPED DOWN

40
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:39,028
AND IT ACCIDENTALLY
BURST MY SCHOOL RING

41
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:41,364
- BETWEEN MY THIGHS.
- OH, YEAH.

42
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:44,284
AND THEN YOU KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED?

43
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:46,286
Tony:
<i>What happened?</i>

44
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:50,164
Woman:
<i>I was in the perfect</i>
<i>place</i>

45
00:04:50,164 --> 00:04:54,377
<i>between sleeping</i>
<i>and dreaming.</i>

46
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:57,171
<i>I slowly felt</i>
<i>your hands</i>

47
00:04:57,171 --> 00:04:59,173
<i>stroking me,</i>

48
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:02,593
<i>caressing me gently...</i>

49
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:05,096
<i>Then...</i>

50
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:07,223
ARE YOU MAINTAINING
TONIGHT, PARTNER?

51
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:09,225
HMM?

52
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:12,020
OH, YEAH, I'M FINE, MAN.
I'M FINE.

53
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,855
JUST TURN IT UP
A LITTLE BIT.

54
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:16,899
WHAT, ARE YOU
A PERVERT?

55
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:20,486
THIS IS LIKE SOME BAD
PENTHOUSE LETTER.

56
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:23,614
IT'S PERFECT IF YOUR
BOYFRIEND'S A CHEESEBALL

57
00:05:23,614 --> 00:05:25,742
LIKE TONY D.

58
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:34,751
HEY.

59
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:39,797
( honks horn )

60
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:41,883
( muffled gunshot )

61
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,677
WHAT WAS THAT?

62
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:46,721
SHIT.

63
00:05:47,972 --> 00:05:49,891
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

64
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,310
<i>WHERE ARE YOU GOING?</i>

65
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:54,854
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.
CALL FOR BACKUP.

66
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:59,525
<i>( Tony and woman moaning )</i>

67
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,615
( woman screams )

68
00:06:05,615 --> 00:06:08,159
( rapid gunfire )

69
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:30,098
MAKE IT FAST.

70
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:42,527
( tires screech )

71
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:49,784
POLICE!

72
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,499
- ANYONE ELSE IN HERE?
- HUH-UH.

73
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:58,584
- NO?
- NO.

74
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:03,423
TONY FUCKING D.

75
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:06,342
SIX MONTHS
DOWN THE DRAIN.

76
00:07:06,342 --> 00:07:09,011
COME HERE.

77
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:13,141
SIT DOWN.

78
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,143
YOU ALL RIGHT?

79
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,145
- I THINK SO.
- GOOD.

80
00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:19,480
FACES-- WHAT DID THEY
LOOK LIKE?

81
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,816
<i>FACES, YOU KNOW?</i>

82
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:23,568
YOU'RE NOT GOING MUTE
ON ME, ARE YOU?

83
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:26,737
LOOK, IT WAS A PERFECT DATE.
I THINK I'LL ORDER PIZZA.

84
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:29,615
YOU MUST BE THE SENTIMENTAL
TYPE, HUH, ALMA?

85
00:07:29,615 --> 00:07:33,286
SO YOU KNOW MY NAME.

86
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:36,038
YOU KNOW WHAT IT MEANS?

87
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:38,040
NOT A FUCKING CLUE,
BUT I KNOW TONY OVER THERE--

88
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,917
HE PAYS FOR THIS PLACE,
DON'T HE?

89
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:41,919
<i>SO YOU'VE BEEN</i>
<i>WATCHING ME.</i>

90
00:07:41,919 --> 00:07:43,296
THAT'S CREEPY.

91
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,131
YOU PUT ON
SUCH A NICE SHOW.

92
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:48,759
HE PAID FOR YOU TOO?
HOURLY OR WEEKLY?

93
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:51,554
HEY, JACK, EASE UP.

94
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:53,556
HEY, PHIL.

95
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:56,392
MEET ALMA.

96
00:07:56,392 --> 00:08:01,355
BE VERY GENTLE WITH HER.
SHE'S QUITE UPSET.

97
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:28,508
Jack:
<i>HOW DOES THIS GET TO BE</i>
<i>MY FUCK-UP?</i>

98
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:30,801
YOU WERE
SITTING ON YOUR ASS
20' AWAY, JACK.

99
00:08:30,801 --> 00:08:33,221
WE WERE THERE
TO MONITOR ONLY.
IT'S NOT OUR FAULT

100
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:35,223
IF TONY DOESN'T TAKE
POLICE PROTECTION.

101
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,225
I DON'T CARE.
BOTTOM LINE IS,

102
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:39,852
WE GUARANTEED TONY WOULD
TURN STATE'S EVIDENCE

103
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:42,563
AND SOME HITTER
TAKES HIM OUT RIGHT
UNDER YOUR NOSE.

104
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,565
AND NOW THE MAYOR,
THE D.A.

105
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:46,901
AND THE FUCKING F.B.I.
ESPECIALLY

106
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:49,362
ARE ALL OVER MY BACK.
ARE YOU READY, PHIL?

107
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:51,781
- ALL SET.
- F.B.I.?

108
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:54,116
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE DOING THIS
DOG-AND-PONY SHOW FOR--
BILL KEENAN?

109
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:55,743
<i>THAT'S RIGHT.</i>
- WHY?

110
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:58,162
WHY?
BECAUSE HE WANTS IT.

111
00:08:58,162 --> 00:09:01,207
BUT THAT'S BULLSHIT, MAN.
I HAVE BRIEFED THIS GUY
AT LEAST A DOZEN TIMES MYSELF.

112
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:04,752
LISTEN, THE MAYOR'S
ASKED THE F.B.I. TO RUN
THIS TASK FORCE.

113
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:07,213
KEENAN HAS THE AXE
OVER YOU AND OVER ME.

114
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:09,715
IT'S TIME TO PUCKER UP,
JACK.

115
00:09:11,342 --> 00:09:13,928
SORRY WE'RE LATE.
DOES EVERYBODY KNOW EVERYBODY?

116
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:16,097
SPECIAL AGENT IN CHARGE
BILL KEENAN.

117
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:19,016
AND, BILL, THIS IS HEAD OF
THE ORGANIZED CRIME SQUAD
FRANK JENNINGS

118
00:09:19,016 --> 00:09:22,061
<i>DETECTIVE PHIL KELLY</i>
<i>AND DETECTIVE JACK VALENTINE.</i>

119
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:24,188
'MORNING, COUNSELOR.

120
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:31,112
Phil:
<i>THE NUMBER-TWO MAN</i>
<i>IN THE MASSINO FAMILY,</i>

121
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:33,489
<i>A.K.A. TONY D,</i>

122
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:36,576
SICILIAN, A REAL
OLD-SCHOOL KNEE-BREAKER.

123
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:39,829
<i>WHOEVER TOOK TONY OUT</i>
<i>HAD TO BE AN INSIDER.</i>

124
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:42,248
<i>NO ONE KNEW</i>
<i>ABOUT THE GIRL.</i>

125
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,750
<i>RIGHT NOW</i>
<i>THE BIG QUESTION IS</i>
<i>WHO ON THE INSIDE</i>

126
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:47,712
<i>SENT THOSE HITTERS</i>
<i>TO WHACK OUT TONY D.</i>

127
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:54,260
IS THAT THE GIRL?
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

128
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:55,678
IS SHE COOPERATING?

129
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:57,930
SO FAR JUST NAME, RANK
AND SERIAL NUMBER.

130
00:09:57,930 --> 00:10:00,808
STANDARD ARM PIECE, I'D SAY,
DOES SOME MODELING AROUND TOWN.

131
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:02,852
YEAH, WELL, WITH ALL DUE
RESPECT, KEENAN,

132
00:10:02,852 --> 00:10:05,563
- I THINK SHE'S A LITTLE
MORE THAN THAT.
- YEAH? HOW?

133
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,898
WELL, IN THAT SITUATION
STANDARD ARM PIECE GOES
CATATONIC.

134
00:10:07,898 --> 00:10:09,942
THIS CHICK-- SHE--
SHE HARDLY BLINKED.

135
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:11,235
WHAT'S ON THE TAPES?

136
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:14,155
A LOT OF SEXY STUFF,
OOH-ING AND AH-ING.

137
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:15,823
<i>TONY REALLY HAD IT</i>
<i>FOR THIS GIRL.</i>

138
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:17,825
LET'S FORGET THE GIRL
FOR A SECOND.

139
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,452
SHOW US THE SUSPECTS.

140
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:22,121
<i>WHO DO YOU THINK</i>
<i>ORDERED THE HIT?</i>

141
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:27,710
Phil:
<i>JOE MASSINO,</i>
<i>ALSO KNOWN AS JOE BUDDHA,</i>

142
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,880
HEAD OF THE BUFFALO FARM TEAM
FOR THE CRIME FAMILY
IN NEW YORK CITY.

143
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:33,507
<i>AS BUFFALO'S UNDERBOSS,</i>
<i>HE WAS THE ONLY ONE</i>

144
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:35,968
<i>WHO HAD THE AUTHORITY</i>
<i>TO ISSUE THE HIT</i>
<i>ON TONY D--</i>

145
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,554
<i>THAT IS,</i>
<i>IF THE HIT WAS OFFICIAL.</i>

146
00:10:38,554 --> 00:10:41,807
<i>JOE BUDDHA HAS INTENSE</i>
<i>CONVERSATIONS WITH PARKING</i>
<i>METERS IN LITTLE ITALY.</i>

147
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:44,268
I THINK HE NEEDS HELP
PUTTING ON HIS PANTS
IN THE MORNING.

148
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:46,145
YOU THINK SO?
I DON'T.

149
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:48,564
HE STILL WEARS THE HAT.

150
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:51,025
MAYBE HE FOUND OUT
TONY WAS GONNA TURN
STATE'S EVIDENCE.

151
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,902
YEAH?
AND HOW'D HE DO THAT?

152
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:55,988
HAS TO BE A LEAK.

153
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,742
WHO ELSE YOU GOT?

154
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:02,078
Phil:
<i>WELL, BESIDES JOE,</i>
<i>THE OTHER FAMILY INSIDER</i>

155
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:05,081
<i>WHO MIGHT HAVE SENT</i>
<i>THE HITTERS AFTER TONY D</i>
<i>IS MICHAEL NOCERA.</i>

156
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:08,834
<i>MICHAEL NOCERA,</i>
<i>A.K.A. THE YUPPIE DON.</i>

157
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:11,962
A REAL GENERATION GAP
BETWEEN HIM, TONY AND JOE.

158
00:11:11,962 --> 00:11:14,674
<i>WORD IS, MICHAEL IS ITCHING</i>
<i>TO TAKE JOE BUDDHA'S PLACE</i>

159
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:17,051
<i>AS HEAD OF</i>
<i>THE MASSINO FAMILY. JACK.</i>

160
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:19,136
MICHAEL IS
LIKE THE POSTER BOY
FOR UPWARD MOBILITY.

161
00:11:19,136 --> 00:11:22,098
<i>HE WENT TO PRINCETON...</i>
- TILL THEY KICKED HIM OUT.

162
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:24,433
...DEVELOPS REAL ESTATE,
HAS A PIECE OF A
RECORD COMPANY,

163
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:26,811
<i>PULLS IN A COUPLE</i>
<i>EXTRA MILLION A WEEK</i>

164
00:11:26,811 --> 00:11:29,939
FOR JOE BUDDHA
AND THE LATE TONY D
IN THE GASOLINE TAX SCAM.

165
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:32,983
THE COUNTY, STATE AND FEDS
ALL COLLECT TAX
ON GASOLINE.

166
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:36,195
NOCERA RUNS 300 MILLION
GALLONS A MONTH THROUGH
FIVE STATES.

167
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:39,448
COLLECTS THE TAX,
CLOSES IT DOWN AND
KEEPS THE TAXES.

168
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,450
<i>SHELL COMPANIES</i>
<i>WITHIN SHELL COMPANIES,</i>

169
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:44,161
<i>REGISTERED BACK TO SOME GUY</i>
<i>NAMED JUAN IN PANAMA--</i>

170
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:46,580
YESTERDAY'S NEWS,
OLD HAT.

171
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:56,632
MAYBE TONY HAS A BEEF
WITH SOMEBODY IN NEW YORK
OR LAS VEGAS.

172
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:58,634
LIKE WHO?

173
00:11:58,634 --> 00:12:00,594
YOU GOT NOTHING,
GENTLEMEN.

174
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:02,722
YOU'RE GRASPING AT STRAWS.

175
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:06,100
EXCUSE ME, KEENAN,
WEREN'T YOU THE ONE THAT WANTED
O.C. SHOW-AND-TELL DAY?

176
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,811
WHAT I WANT TO KNOW
IS WHY A DETECTIVE
WITH VALENTINE'S HISTORY

177
00:12:08,811 --> 00:12:11,063
WAS TAKEN OFF A DESK
FOR SOMETHING THIS BIG.

178
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:14,066
ALL DUE RESPECT,
IT'S WHERE HE BELONGS.

179
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:16,068
JACK'S THE ONE
KNOWS THESE GUYS.

180
00:12:16,068 --> 00:12:17,987
HE'S GOT ALL
THE RELATIONSHIPS.

181
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,322
YEAH, PLUS
HE'S A GOOD COP.

182
00:12:20,322 --> 00:12:22,283
WELL, HE USED TO BE,
SURE,

183
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:24,285
BUT I NEED SOMEBODY WHO'S
HITTING ON ALL CYLINDERS.

184
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:26,746
IF JACK MAY SPEAK
FOR HIMSELF FOR A MINUTE,

185
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:31,459
KEENAN,
THAT'S ALL HISTORY.

186
00:12:31,459 --> 00:12:34,754
IT TOOK YOU
SIX GODDAMN MONTHS
TO SET UP TONY D.

187
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:36,964
- YOU'VE ONLY GOT TWO WEEKS.
- FOR WHAT?

188
00:12:36,964 --> 00:12:39,800
TO GET ME SOMETHING
TO ROLL THESE GUYS UP.

189
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,011
YOU KNOW,
YOU GLIDE UP IN HERE
THREATENING PEOPLE.

190
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:44,680
YOU THREATEN FRANK.
AND NOW YOU START
THREATENING ME.

191
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,349
JACK.

192
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,941
I'M COOL, MAN.

193
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:58,861
TWO WEEKS, THAT'S IT.

194
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:00,738
WHAT DO YOU SAY, JACK?

195
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:04,992
- I SAY WE FIND THE LEAK.
<i>WHERE DO YOU START?</i>

196
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:08,954
TONY D'S GIRL IS
AS GOOD A PLACE AS NAY.

197
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:10,956
THAT'S A WASTE OF TIME.

198
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:14,877
WELL, RIGHT NOW, KEENAN,
THAT'S ALL WE GOT.

199
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:18,464
OKAY.

200
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:21,008
BUT DON'T COME BEGGING
FOR YOUR JOB BACK

201
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:23,093
WHEN IT DOESN'T
WORK OUT.

202
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,808
GENTLEMEN, COUNSELOR.

203
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:37,024
DETECTIVE VALENTINE,
COULD I HAVE A WORD WITH YOU?

204
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,653
THANK YOU,
DETECTIVE KELLY.

205
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:55,709
WELL, THAT CERTAINLY
WAS FUN.

206
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:58,003
WHAT IF KEENAN COMES BACK
FOR HIS BOW TIE?

207
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:00,464
I DON'T CARE ABOUT KEENAN.
I CARE ABOUT YOU.

208
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:03,050
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'VE LOST
A LOT OF WEIGHT.

209
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,719
WELL, THE NICE THING ABOUT
A LITTLE ANXIETY

210
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,763
IS YOU LOSE WEIGHT WITHOUT
HAVING TO DO ON A DIET.

211
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:11,267
AND YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE NOT
GETTING ENOUGH SLEEP EITHER.

212
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,602
ARE YOU STILL HAVING
THOSE DREAMS?

213
00:14:13,602 --> 00:14:16,146
- YOU MEAN THE NIGHTMARES?
- MM-HMM.

214
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:18,148
A TRIPLE FEATURE
EVERY NIGHT.

215
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:20,276
YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD
LET ME COOK YOU DINNER

216
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,987
LATER ON IN THE WEEK.

217
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:25,406
I THOUGHT WE WEREN'T
DOING THAT ANYMORE.

218
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:27,992
JACK, IT'S JUST DINNER,

219
00:14:27,992 --> 00:14:29,994
NOT YOUR HAND
IN MARRIAGE.

220
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,370
THINK ABOUT IT.

221
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:41,547
OH, HI, SUGAR PIE.
NOW WHAT ARE YOU DOING
BACK DOWN HERE?

222
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:45,801
WELL, I MISSED YOU.
AND I WANTED TO GET
A LITTLE INFORMATION.

223
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:48,596
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

224
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,598
- A WOMAN NAMED ALMA ANSON.
- OKAY.

225
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:53,601
NOW SHE'S A WITNESS
IN THE TONY DENISIO
MURDER CASE.

226
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:55,603
WHAT DO YOU WANT
TO KNOW?

227
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:57,688
ANY LITTLE TIDBIT
YOU CAN GET ME.

228
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:02,151
<i>♪ WHEN THEY TURN</i>
<i>THE LIGHTS OUT ♪</i>

229
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:04,570
<i>♪ THE FACE IS</i>
<i>IN THE SHADOW... ♪</i>

230
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,572
WE'RE FINE.

231
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,574
- HEY, HO, HO.
- HEY, JACK.

232
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:12,828
- YOU LOOK GREAT, MAN.
- HOLY SHIT. WELL...

233
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:15,873
- HEY, A DRINK, COME ON.
- NO, NO, NOT RIGHT NOW.
NO, NO, I--

234
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:17,499
- HEY, TOMMY, TOMMY.
- WHAT?

235
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:19,418
LET ME TALK TO YOU A SECOND.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

236
00:15:19,418 --> 00:15:21,045
ABOUT WHAT?

237
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:23,172
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
ABOUT WHAT?
ABOUT TONY.

238
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:26,216
OH, FUCK, IT'S CRAZY.
IT'S NUTS, MAN.

239
00:15:26,216 --> 00:15:28,218
NO, NO, NO, NO,
TOMMY, TOMMY,

240
00:15:28,218 --> 00:15:31,180
NOW HOW'S YOUR
BROTHER DOING?

241
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:33,182
GREAT.
VINCENT'S DOING GREAT.

242
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:35,559
THAT'S GOOD, 'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,
IT SEEMS MAYBE YOU FORGOT

243
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:38,395
- I HELPED HIM OUT
WITH HIS EARLY PAROLE.
- HEY, I AIN'T FORGOT.

244
00:15:38,395 --> 00:15:40,814
YOU WERE GREAT, DETECTIVE.
YOU WERE A BIG HELP, OKAY?

245
00:15:40,814 --> 00:15:43,317
OKAY, THEN HELP ME OUT.
TOMMY, GIVE ME SOMETHING.

246
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:46,028
I KNOW YOU'VE SEEN
THIS KIND OF SHIT BEFORE.
TELL ME ABOUT TONY.

247
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:49,782
YEAH, I THINK IT'S
ONE OF THOSE THINGS,
YOU KNOW--

248
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,992
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA
FIND OUT WHO DID
ALL OF THIS.

249
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:54,703
LIKE MAYBE 20 YEARS
FROM NOW, YOU KNOW,
YOU MIGHT FIND OUT THAT--

250
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:57,539
TOMMY, TOMMY,
I AIN'T GOT 20 YEARS.
TELL ME SOMETHING.

251
00:15:57,539 --> 00:16:00,042
WHAT ABOUT THAT TALL,
SKINNY BLOND GIRL
HE WAS SEEING?

252
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:02,795
I'M BEING
HONEST HERE, JACK.
WHAT CAN I TELL YOU?

253
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:04,421
I GOTTA GO.

254
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:07,675
- TOMMY.
- CALL ME, CALL ME.

255
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:10,052
<i>( crows cawing )</i>
- ( speaking Latin )

256
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:12,179
<i>( camera shutter</i>
<i>clicking )</i>

257
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:28,779
HEY, HEY, LOOK WHO'S PAYING
MICHAEL NOCERA A VISIT.

258
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:32,658
YEAH, TONY D'S
NUMBER-ONE GUYS.

259
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:35,869
<i>HE SEEM HAPPY ABOUT IT</i>
<i>TO YOU?</i>

260
00:16:35,869 --> 00:16:38,580
IT'S A FUNERAL, JACK.
HE'S NOT SUPPOSED TO
LOOK HAPPY.

261
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:41,208
NO, MAN, THAT'S BULLSHIT.
THEY'RE LEANING ON HIM, MAN.

262
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:46,422
THREE-TO-TWO IT'S 'CAUSE
NO ONE KNOWS FOR SURE

263
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,424
WHO KILLED TONY D.

264
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:51,301
WHAT, YOU THINK NOCERA?
HE'S NOT THAT STUPID.

265
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:58,058
Jack:
<i>HEY, MAN, HOLD ON NOW.</i>

266
00:16:59,977 --> 00:17:02,688
<i>HEY, LOOK WHO</i>
<i>SHOWED UP.</i>

267
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,488
GOD DAMN.

268
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,536
- YOU BITCH.
- UH-OH.

269
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:19,997
YOU BITCH.
WHORE!

270
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:22,458
HOW DARE YOU?
HOW DARE YOU?

271
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:25,669
<i>WHO DO YOU THINK</i>
<i>YOU ARE?</i>

272
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:49,943
HEY, WHATEVER YOU'RE
THINKING, DON'T DO IT.

273
00:17:49,943 --> 00:17:53,405
PHIL, THEY KNOW WE'RE HERE.
I'M JUST GONNA RATTLE
THE CAGE A LITTLE BIT.

274
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,949
- WHAT THE HELL FOR?
- TO PISS OF THE WILD ANIMALS.

275
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:57,910
- NOW TRUST ME ON THIS.
I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.
- JACK.

276
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:09,004
SON OF A BITCH.

277
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:12,174
OH, SORRY,
I'M A LITTLE LATE.

278
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:15,344
A GUY IS DEAD.
NOW THIS IS ALL BULLSHIT.

279
00:18:15,344 --> 00:18:18,138
YOU ARE OUT OF ORDER.

280
00:18:18,138 --> 00:18:20,182
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
JOEY, JOEY, TECHNICALLY

281
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:21,809
I HAD A RELATIONSHIP
WITH TONY TOO.

282
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:23,811
<i>I CAN'T PAY</i>
<i>MY LAST RESPECTS?</i>

283
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:25,354
WHAT DID I SAY?

284
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:27,898
<i>JUST LEAVE US</i>
<i>THE FUCK ALONE.</i>

285
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:31,777
ALL RIGHT.

286
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:34,321
I CAN SEE WHEN
I'M NOT WANTED.

287
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:36,824
OKAY.
MICHAEL, FELLOWS.

288
00:18:54,883 --> 00:18:56,885
( sighs )

289
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:59,346
THE GUY GIVES ME
A LARGE PAIN.

290
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:02,474
YOU KNOW THAT MAN?

291
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:05,727
A LONG TIME AGO,

292
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,729
FROM THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

293
00:19:07,729 --> 00:19:09,189
IS THAT ALL?

294
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:11,191
HE USED TO BE AROUND
ALL THE TIME,

295
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:14,027
ALWAYS POKING
HIS NOSE IN.

296
00:19:14,027 --> 00:19:16,613
YEAH.

297
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:19,449
HOW GOOD DO YOU KNOW HIM?

298
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:23,162
JUST ANOTHER HUMP
WITH A BADGE, JOE.

299
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:37,593
YOU SEE ANYTHING IN THERE,
ANYONE YOU RECOGNIZE?

300
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:40,053
HUH-UH, SORRY.
IT ALL HAPPENED
TOO QUICKLY.

301
00:19:40,053 --> 00:19:42,806
( through speaker )
I didn't get a good look.

302
00:19:42,806 --> 00:19:44,474
Okay.

303
00:19:44,474 --> 00:19:46,476
WHAT SCHOOL
DID YOU GO TO?

304
00:19:46,476 --> 00:19:48,854
ST. MARY'S, BOSTON,
TILL THEY KICKED ME OUT

305
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:50,731
FOR TALKING BACK
TO THE NUNS.

306
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:54,067
MM. FAMILY?

307
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:03,952
DOES IT UPSET YOU IF I ASK
YOU ABOUT YOUR FAMILY?

308
00:20:03,952 --> 00:20:06,997
YOU CAN'T UPSET ME,
DETECTIVE.

309
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,750
GOOD.

310
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,085
IF YOU MUST KNOW, MY MOTHER
DIED WHEN I WAS FIVE.

311
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:13,962
MY FATHER DIED
WHEN I WAS EIGHT.

312
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:19,009
How long have you
known Tony D?

313
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:21,845
- ONE MONTH.
- WHERE DID YOU MEET?

314
00:20:21,845 --> 00:20:24,348
WHERE THE GIRLS
MEET THE BOYS--
AT SOME PARTY.

315
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:28,602
DID IT MAYBE BOTHER YOU
WHO HE WAS?

316
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:33,273
DID IT MAYBE BOTHER YOU
THAT THAT WITNESS
GOT KILLED--

317
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:36,610
THAT LADY YOU WERE
SUPPOSE TO PROTECT?

318
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:44,910
DOES IT UPSET YOU
WHEN I ASK YOU ABOUT
YOUR PAST, DETECTIVE?

319
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:49,414
WHY DON'T WE JUST STAY
FOCUSED ON YOU?

320
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:50,999
YOU'RE UPSET,

321
00:20:50,999 --> 00:20:53,877
but you can't show it.

322
00:20:53,877 --> 00:20:57,589
JUST ANSWER
MY QUESTIONS.

323
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:00,968
WHY DID TONY D COME
TO YOUR HOUSE THAT NIGHT?

324
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,803
WHY DID YOUR WIFE
LEAVE YOU?

325
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:04,805
COUNSEL, YOU WANT
TO TELL YOUR CLIENT
TO QUIT PLAYING GAMES

326
00:21:04,805 --> 00:21:06,807
AND ANSWER
MY QUESTIONS?

327
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:10,519
( whispers )

328
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:14,940
MEN LIKE TONY DON'T TALK
TO WOMEN LIKE ME
ABOUT BUSINESS.

329
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:17,859
AND WHAT DID YOU THINK
TONY'S BUSINESS WAS?

330
00:21:17,859 --> 00:21:20,112
DO I LOOK STUPID
TO YOU, DETECTIVE?

331
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:22,114
I KNEW EXACTLY
WHAT TONY WAS.

332
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,533
HE WAS GOOD TO ME
AND TIMES ARE TOUGH.

333
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:27,703
<i>SO IF YOU'RE GONNA</i>
<i>CHARGE ME WITH SOMETHING,</i>
<i>YOU GO RIGHT AHEAD.</i>

334
00:21:27,703 --> 00:21:30,747
OTHERWISE I WOULD LIKE
TO LEAVE.

335
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:38,422
GO AHEAD.
I'M THROUGH WITH YOU FOR NOW.

336
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:42,926
THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME.

337
00:22:04,948 --> 00:22:07,159
( gasps )
OH, YOU SCARED ME.

338
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:09,202
- HOW DID YOU GET IN?
<i>( music playing )</i>

339
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:10,954
I STILL GOT MINE.

340
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:13,582
OH.

341
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:16,710
FLOWERS--
OH, THEY'RE BEAUTIFUL.

342
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:18,795
- HI.
- HI.

343
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:22,591
LET ME DO THIS
FOR YOU.

344
00:22:22,591 --> 00:22:25,385
GO AHEAD.
WAS THERE TRAFFIC?

345
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:27,012
NO, IT WAS COOL.

346
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:29,097
GET YOUR JACKET?

347
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,522
( sighs )

348
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:39,691
WOULD YOU LIKE
SOME WINE?

349
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:41,818
NO, SHIT.

350
00:22:45,113 --> 00:22:48,909
YOU KNOW, THERE'S SOMETHING
ABOUT A MAN IN THE KITCHEN

351
00:22:48,909 --> 00:22:51,495
THAT REALLY
TURNS ME ON.

352
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:54,039
REMEMBER WHAT WE SAID?

353
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:56,416
NO, I DON'T REMEMBER.

354
00:23:04,883 --> 00:23:06,968
JACK.

355
00:23:08,178 --> 00:23:10,305
LET'S GO UPSTAIRS.

356
00:24:06,111 --> 00:24:07,904
HEY.

357
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:11,867
JACK?

358
00:24:20,792 --> 00:24:24,087
YOU KNOW, YOU'D BETTER
QUIT BLAMING YOURSELF.

359
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:27,340
OKAY, SO YOU GOT TOO CLOSE
TO A WITNESS-- NOT SMART.

360
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:29,926
BUT YOU DIDN'T PULL
THE TRIGGER.

361
00:24:29,926 --> 00:24:32,304
ARE YOU GONNA SEND ME
A BILL FOR ALL THIS
FREE ANALYSIS?

362
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:36,600
NO, SHE KNEW IT WAS
DANGEROUS TO WEAR A WIRE.

363
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,227
SHE WANTED TO DO IT.

364
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:48,820
IT WOULD PROBABLY BE BETTER
IF WHEN YOU CAME HERE

365
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:51,531
YOU WERE READY
TO BE HERE.

366
00:25:40,038 --> 00:25:42,916
THE SEA LION'S
GONNA GET YOU.

367
00:25:43,959 --> 00:25:46,545
IT'S GONNA GET YOU.

368
00:25:51,967 --> 00:25:53,969
<i>( applause )</i>

369
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:56,179
<i>♪ Rainy days</i>
<i>and lonely nights ♪</i>

370
00:25:56,179 --> 00:25:58,431
<i>♪ I feel... ♪</i>

371
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:07,440
<i>♪ All my affection</i>
<i>I gave onto you ♪</i>

372
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:09,859
<i>♪ Your smile</i>
<i>brings me joy ♪</i>

373
00:26:09,859 --> 00:26:13,780
<i>♪ Your love makes me</i>
<i>happy ♪</i>

374
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:17,200
<i>♪ You know</i>
<i>that wherever I am ♪</i>

375
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,995
<i>♪ I'll run to you ♪</i>

376
00:26:19,995 --> 00:26:23,790
<i>♪ For you are</i>
<i>my love, you ♪</i>

377
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:26,710
<i>♪ 'Cause you bring me</i>
<i>sunshine ♪</i>

378
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:29,004
<i>♪ In the rain ♪</i>

379
00:26:29,004 --> 00:26:33,842
<i>♪ You bring me joy</i>
<i>when I feel in pain ♪</i>

380
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:35,969
<i>♪ When I am down ♪</i>

381
00:26:35,969 --> 00:26:38,555
<i>♪ And feel alone... ♪</i>

382
00:26:40,056 --> 00:26:42,851
THANK YOU.
EXCUSE ME.

383
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:46,396
( knocks )
HEY.

384
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:50,191
REMEMBER ME?

385
00:26:54,654 --> 00:26:57,032
OH, WHO ARE YOU
GONNA CALL?

386
00:26:57,032 --> 00:26:59,034
MY ATTORNEY.
WHO DO YOU THINK?

387
00:26:59,034 --> 00:27:00,702
OH, YOU DON'T NEED
TO DO THAT.

388
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:03,538
THIS IS AN UNOFFICIAL
VISIT, IF THAT'S OKAY.

389
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:06,833
WELL, I BELIEVE I'VE ANSWERED
ALL YOUR QUESTIONS ALREADY.

390
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:09,210
I HAVE ONE MORE.

391
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:14,132
OKAY, WELL, I'VE GOT
ONE QUESTION FOR YOU TOO.

392
00:27:16,801 --> 00:27:19,054
- ( clicks )
- YOU FIRST.

393
00:27:20,597 --> 00:27:22,891
WHAT'S WITH THE RECORDER?

394
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:24,893
PROTECTION.

395
00:27:24,893 --> 00:27:28,313
I ALWAYS LIKE
TO BE PROTECTED.

396
00:27:28,313 --> 00:27:31,274
RIGHT, QUESTION:

397
00:27:31,274 --> 00:27:35,737
WHY WOULD WHOEVER KILLED
TONY D LEAVE YOU ALIVE?

398
00:27:35,737 --> 00:27:38,365
SO YOU THINK
I'M IN DANGER?

399
00:27:42,118 --> 00:27:44,120
WELL, I THINK
THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE

400
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:46,122
THAT THEY'RE GONNA COME
PAY YOU A VISIT, YEAH.

401
00:27:46,122 --> 00:27:49,376
WELL, I'M NOT
THAT WORRIED.

402
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:51,544
<i>WELL, I JUST THOUGHT</i>
<i>YOU MIGHT THINK</i>

403
00:27:51,544 --> 00:27:53,922
IT WAS A GOOD IDEA
TO HAVE A FRIEND
THAT WAS A COP.

404
00:27:53,922 --> 00:27:56,758
WHAT EXACTLY DO YOU MEAN
BY "FRIEND"?

405
00:27:56,758 --> 00:28:00,011
FRIEND-- I TALK, YOU TALK,
THAT KIND OF STUFF.

406
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:02,055
WELL, FRIENDSHIP IS
SOMETHING YOU FEEL.

407
00:28:02,055 --> 00:28:04,057
<i>IT'S SOMETHING</i>
<i>IN YOUR SOUL.</i>

408
00:28:04,057 --> 00:28:06,518
IT'S NOT AN EXCHANGE
FOR A PAYOFF.

409
00:28:06,518 --> 00:28:09,062
ARE YOU STILL WATCHING ME,
DETECTIVE?

410
00:28:10,563 --> 00:28:12,565
I THINK YOU HAVE
SOMETHING A LITTLE MORE

411
00:28:12,565 --> 00:28:15,235
INTERESTING IN MIND
THAN JUST FRIENDS.

412
00:28:15,235 --> 00:28:19,447
YOU KNOW, THIS--
THIS MIGHT COME
AS A TOTAL SURPRISE,

413
00:28:19,447 --> 00:28:22,826
BUT I DON'T FIND
YOUR TALL, LANKY ASS
IRRESISTIBLE AT ALL.

414
00:28:22,826 --> 00:28:26,955
LOOK, BOYS AND GIRLS
IS THE SUBJECT I'M NEVER
WRONG ABOUT.

415
00:28:26,955 --> 00:28:28,957
<i>ME,</i>
DO YOU?

416
00:28:28,957 --> 00:28:30,959
NO, I DON'T KNOW YOU
PERSONALLY,

417
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:34,671
BUT THE WORLD'S FULL OF MEN
THAT WANT TO BE MY FRIEND.

418
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:37,132
ALL RIGHT.

419
00:28:37,132 --> 00:28:39,426
IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND
AND YOU DECIDE

420
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:41,886
<i>YOU CAN USE ONE MORE</i>
<i>MAN FRIEND</i>

421
00:28:41,886 --> 00:28:43,930
IN THE WORLD OF MEN
THAT WANT TO BE
YOUR FRIENDS,

422
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:45,932
MY NUMBER'S
IN THE BACK.

423
00:28:45,932 --> 00:28:47,934
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR TIME.

424
00:28:47,934 --> 00:28:49,936
OH, ONE MORE THING:

425
00:28:49,936 --> 00:28:52,605
UH, HOW DID YOU KNOW

426
00:28:52,605 --> 00:28:54,607
THAT PERSONAL STUFF
ABOUT ME?

427
00:28:54,607 --> 00:28:57,610
YOU, YOUR WITNESS,
YOUR BREAKDOWN--

428
00:28:57,610 --> 00:29:00,697
COME ON, JACK,
