00:42:47,648 --> 00:42:49,650
I GOT NO BUTTONS
LEFT TO PUSH.

644
00:42:49,650 --> 00:42:51,610
WANT TO BET?

645
00:42:51,610 --> 00:42:55,239
SEE, NOW MICHAEL AND TONY--
THEY MAY LIKE ALL THIS,

646
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:59,493
BUT ME-- YOU NEED TO FIND
YOURSELF ANOTHER SUCKER.

647
00:42:59,493 --> 00:43:02,079
WHAT, ARE YOU AFRAID
OF ME?

648
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:09,587
YOU CAME BY HERE
TO TELL ME SOMETHING.

649
00:43:09,587 --> 00:43:12,006
WHY DON'T YOU
CUT TO THE CHASE?

650
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:17,678
WHAT IF YOU DON'T LIKE
WHAT YOU HEAR?

651
00:43:17,678 --> 00:43:21,056
LIKE WHAT YOU TOLD
MICHAEL NOCERA TO GET HIM
TO KILL TONY D?

652
00:43:21,056 --> 00:43:25,019
YOU'RE GIVING ME
TOO MUCH CREDIT, JACK.

653
00:43:25,019 --> 00:43:27,646
THEY'RE JUST
NATURAL PREDATORS.

654
00:43:34,612 --> 00:43:36,614
SO WHAT WOULD MICHAEL
THE NATURAL PREDATOR

655
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:39,033
THINK OF YOU
WITH ME RIGHT NOW?

656
00:43:39,033 --> 00:43:43,579
<i>IT'S OVER.</i>
<i>HE'S IN THE PAST.</i>

657
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:45,581
WHY DON'T I
BELIEVE YOU?

658
00:43:45,581 --> 00:43:48,459
BECAUSE YOU'RE A COP.
IT'S YOUR JOB.

659
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:51,295
<i>( phone ringing )</i>

660
00:43:53,505 --> 00:43:55,549
<i>( answering machine</i>
<i>clicks )</i>

661
00:43:55,549 --> 00:43:57,551
<i>Hi. This is Jack.</i>
<i>Please leave a message</i>
<i>after the beep.</i>

662
00:43:57,551 --> 00:43:59,178
<i>( machine beeps )</i>

663
00:43:59,178 --> 00:44:01,180
Woman:
<i>Jack, I know you're there.</i>

664
00:44:01,180 --> 00:44:03,307
<i>Pick up, come on.</i>
<i>We need to talk.</i>

665
00:44:03,307 --> 00:44:06,060
SOUNDS LIKE SOMEBODY
NEEDS TO TALK TO YOU
PRETTY BAD.

666
00:44:06,060 --> 00:44:08,812
<i>Jack, pick up.</i>
- EXCUSE ME A MINUTE.

667
00:44:08,812 --> 00:44:10,814
<i>Jack, I'm not</i>
<i>gonna hang up.</i>

668
00:44:10,814 --> 00:44:13,317
<i>Pick up.</i>
<i>Come on, we need to talk.</i>

669
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:15,778
<i>Jack, pick up the phone.</i>

670
00:44:15,778 --> 00:44:17,946
YEAH.

671
00:44:17,946 --> 00:44:20,115
NO, NO, I JUST RAN
THE PHOTO.

672
00:44:22,785 --> 00:44:25,788
CAN I CALL YOU BACK
IN FIVE MINUTES?

673
00:44:25,788 --> 00:44:28,582
RIGHT, YEAH,
I'LL CALL YOU
IN FIVE MINUTES.

674
00:44:28,582 --> 00:44:29,917
RIGHT.

675
00:44:36,757 --> 00:44:38,842
ALMA?

676
00:44:53,607 --> 00:44:56,819
Jack:
<i>THIS GIRL'S READY</i>
<i>TO TALK.</i>

677
00:44:56,819 --> 00:44:59,113
NOW WE'VE GOT
A BREAK HERE.
LET'S ROLL WITH IT.

678
00:44:59,113 --> 00:45:01,782
WHAT BREAK? SHE COMES
TO YOUR HOUSE. SHE SAYS
SHE WANTS TO HAVE DINNER.

679
00:45:01,782 --> 00:45:04,368
WHAT, ALL OF A SUDDEN
SHE FINDS YOU A WITTY
CONVERSATIONALIST?

680
00:45:04,368 --> 00:45:06,203
<i>JESUS.</i>

681
00:45:06,203 --> 00:45:08,330
IS THERE SOMETHING GOING ON
BETWEEN YOU AND THIS WITNESS

682
00:45:08,330 --> 00:45:10,207
THAT I NEED TO KNOW
ABOUT, JACK?

683
00:45:10,207 --> 00:45:12,209
NO.

684
00:45:12,209 --> 00:45:16,922
I'M CULTIVATING
AN INFORMANT, THAT'S IT.

685
00:45:16,922 --> 00:45:19,007
OKAY.

686
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:23,762
LOOK, JACK WILL BE
WEARING A WIRE.

687
00:45:23,762 --> 00:45:26,223
I'LL BE IN THE TRUCK.
WE'LL GET EVERY WORD
ON TAPE.

688
00:45:26,223 --> 00:45:27,975
I MEAN, IT'S WORTH
A SHOT.

689
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:30,602
Keenan:
<i>ALL THIS GIRLFRIEND SHIT</i>
<i>IS MARGINAL.</i>

690
00:45:30,602 --> 00:45:33,564
TONY WAS SERVING US JOE
ON A PLATTER. HE FOUND OUT
ABOUT IT AND ICED HIM.

691
00:45:33,564 --> 00:45:35,899
- IT'S REAL SIMPLE.
- IT WAS MICHAEL NOCERA.

692
00:45:35,899 --> 00:45:37,901
- REALLY?
- REALLY.

693
00:45:37,901 --> 00:45:40,237
LOOK, ALMA ANSON
IS NOT EVEN A REAL NAME.

694
00:45:40,237 --> 00:45:42,823
<i>SHE IS DYING</i>
<i>TO GIVE ME SOMETHING</i>

695
00:45:42,823 --> 00:45:45,284
I CAN USE TO SQUEEZE
MICHAEL NOCERA WITH.
I FEEL IT.

696
00:45:45,284 --> 00:45:47,411
<i>LET'S JUST GET IT</i>
<i>ON TAPE.</i>

697
00:45:49,663 --> 00:45:52,332
NOCERA WOULD
SELL OUT HIS GRANDMOTHER
TO AVOID GOING TO JAIL.

698
00:45:52,332 --> 00:45:55,627
WE PUT A LITTLE
PRESSURE ON HIM, I THINK
HE'D GIVE US JOE BUDDHA.

699
00:45:55,627 --> 00:45:58,464
YEAH. YOU KNOW,
I THINK I LIKED
THESE GUYS BETTER

700
00:45:58,464 --> 00:46:00,340
WHEN THEY HAD
THE CODE OF SILENCE.
( chuckles )

701
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:02,676
NO SHIT.

702
00:46:04,094 --> 00:46:06,221
OKAY, I'LL GO WITH IT,

703
00:46:06,221 --> 00:46:08,223
BUT I WANT EVERYTHING
OFFICIAL AND ON RECORD.

704
00:46:08,223 --> 00:46:11,226
AND I'M THE ONLY ONE
WHO CUTS A DEAL.

705
00:46:15,689 --> 00:46:19,485
SO TELL ME A LITTLE BIT
ABOUT THIS TONY FELLOW.

706
00:46:19,485 --> 00:46:21,528
TONY CAME INTO MY LIFE

707
00:46:21,528 --> 00:46:23,572
AT A TIME WHEN I REALLY
NEEDED SOMEBODY.

708
00:46:23,572 --> 00:46:26,033
<i>Tony was a very</i>
<i>controlling man.</i>

709
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:28,160
<i>He had to know where</i>
<i>I was all the time.</i>

710
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:29,787
<i>So he was</i>
<i>a control freak.</i>

711
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:31,747
<i>( chuckles )</i>
<i>He was a control freak,</i>
<i>yeah.</i>

712
00:46:31,747 --> 00:46:35,292
SO YOU STARTED AN AFFAIR
WITH A CONTROL FREAK'S
BUSINESS PARTNER.

713
00:46:35,292 --> 00:46:37,795
WELL, IT WASN'T SMART,

714
00:46:37,795 --> 00:46:41,548
BUT I THINK
YOU OF ALL PEOPLE
SHOULD UNDERSTAND THAT.

715
00:46:41,548 --> 00:46:43,675
( chuckles )
NO, LET'S LEAVE JACK
OUT OF THIS.

716
00:46:43,675 --> 00:46:47,054
I'M THE LAST ONE TO PASS
JUDGMENT ON ANYBODY.

717
00:46:47,054 --> 00:46:51,558
MM, SOUNDS LIKE
THE KIND OF GUY I NEED.

718
00:46:51,558 --> 00:46:53,936
WHY? YOU GOT
MORE TO HIDE?

719
00:46:53,936 --> 00:46:57,231
CURIOSITY KILLED
THE CAT, JACK.

720
00:46:57,231 --> 00:46:59,107
BUT WHO KILLED TONY D?

721
00:47:04,154 --> 00:47:08,283
DID YOU TELL NOCERA
THAT HE WAS GONNA TURN
STATE'S EVIDENCE?

722
00:47:15,457 --> 00:47:17,918
DON'T BE SUCH A COP.

723
00:47:48,448 --> 00:47:50,784
I-- I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

724
00:48:04,673 --> 00:48:06,800
<i>( static hissing )</i>

725
00:48:07,759 --> 00:48:10,721
JACK, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

726
00:48:22,399 --> 00:48:24,359
( sighs )

727
00:48:25,277 --> 00:48:27,404
<i>( static stops )</i>

728
00:50:39,911 --> 00:50:42,831
- NO.
- HEY.

729
00:50:42,831 --> 00:50:45,500
- GET AWAY.
- HEY.

730
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:47,878
ALMA, WAKE UP.

731
00:50:47,878 --> 00:50:49,880
IT'S ME.

732
00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:51,965
WHAT'S WRONG?

733
00:50:53,383 --> 00:50:55,927
YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW.

734
00:50:58,889 --> 00:51:03,727
LOOK, IT WAS
AN INCREDIBLE NIGHT, OKAY?

735
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:06,855
LET'S JUST LEAVE IT
AT THAT.

736
00:51:14,446 --> 00:51:16,573
<i>( water running )</i>

737
00:52:04,412 --> 00:52:06,123
OH, SHIT.

738
00:52:24,391 --> 00:52:26,518
HOW IS HE FEELING
THIS MORNING?

739
00:52:26,518 --> 00:52:28,520
HE JUST WOKE UP.

740
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:31,356
THIS IS
THE THIRD NIGHT THIS WEEK
HE DIDN'T COME HOME.

741
00:52:31,356 --> 00:52:33,650
YOUR PARTNER'S HERE.

742
00:52:36,069 --> 00:52:38,196
<i>( clock chiming )</i>

743
00:52:39,447 --> 00:52:41,324
GOOD MORNING.

744
00:52:41,324 --> 00:52:42,951
YOU WANT SOME COFFEE?

745
00:52:42,951 --> 00:52:44,828
YEAH, THAT'D BE GREAT.

746
00:52:44,828 --> 00:52:46,830
HERE.

747
00:52:46,830 --> 00:52:48,832
HELP YOURSELF.

748
00:52:48,832 --> 00:52:50,834
I'M HAVING
HERBAL TEA.

749
00:52:53,003 --> 00:52:55,672
- ( dog squealing )
- GO ON.

750
00:52:55,672 --> 00:52:57,674
GO FIND YOUR MOTHER.

751
00:52:57,674 --> 00:52:59,676
SO HOW ARE YOU
FEELING?

752
00:52:59,676 --> 00:53:01,678
HOW AM I FEELING?

753
00:53:01,678 --> 00:53:04,973
WELL, I WAS ON A LISTENING
POST LAST NIGHT

754
00:53:04,973 --> 00:53:07,601
AND SOMEBODY MESSED
WITH MY GEAR.

755
00:53:07,601 --> 00:53:10,770
YEAH, WE NEED TO TALK
ABOUT THAT.

756
00:53:10,770 --> 00:53:13,523
COME ON.

757
00:53:13,523 --> 00:53:16,234
YOU FORGOT ABOUT THE BUG
ON HER CELL PHONE, JACK.

758
00:53:18,153 --> 00:53:19,446
YOU HEARD, HUH?

759
00:53:19,446 --> 00:53:21,448
EVERY LAST WORD.

760
00:53:21,448 --> 00:53:23,450
<i>JUST ERASE</i>
<i>THOSE DAMN TAPES.</i>

761
00:53:23,450 --> 00:53:25,452
JUST-- JUST TELL THEM
THE EQUIPMENT MALFUNCTIONED

762
00:53:25,452 --> 00:53:27,245
LIKE IT DID FOR US
THE OTHER DAY IN THE VAN.

763
00:53:27,245 --> 00:53:30,832
THEY'RE NOT GONNA BUY THAT.
TWICE IN ONE WEEK?
COME ON.

764
00:53:30,832 --> 00:53:32,125
THIS IS MY JOB.

765
00:53:32,125 --> 00:53:34,127
PHIL, I'M YOUR PARTNER.

766
00:53:34,127 --> 00:53:36,838
YOU KNOW I'D DO
THE SAME FOR YOU.
I'D BACK YOU UP.

767
00:53:36,838 --> 00:53:38,465
CAN YOU GIVE ME
A LITTLE BREAK?

768
00:53:38,465 --> 00:53:40,467
I GAVE YOU A BREAK, JACK.

769
00:53:40,467 --> 00:53:42,469
I WENT TO THE MATS
FOR YOU.

770
00:53:42,469 --> 00:53:44,512
YOU KNOW,
AND NOW IT'S BACK
TO THE SAME OLD SHIT.

771
00:53:44,512 --> 00:53:46,598
<i>( footsteps )</i>

772
00:53:48,183 --> 00:53:51,311
YOU SAID YOU'D MAKE
BREAKFAST FOR RUPERT.

773
00:53:51,311 --> 00:53:53,313
( sighs )

774
00:53:53,313 --> 00:53:55,065
IN A SECOND,
HONEY, OKAY?

775
00:53:56,483 --> 00:53:58,652
I'LL GET IT.

776
00:54:03,073 --> 00:54:05,200
I DON'T
BELIEVE THIS, MAN.

777
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:07,202
( chuckles )

778
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:11,831
FIRST TIME OUT OF THE BOX
IN OVER A YEAR AND, WELL--

779
00:54:11,831 --> 00:54:14,042
I JUST HOPE
SHE WAS WORTH IT.

780
00:54:16,461 --> 00:54:18,463
SHE WAS WORTH IT, MAN.

781
00:54:18,463 --> 00:54:22,300
YEAH, WHY DON'T YOU JUST
SHOOT YOURSELF IN THE HEAD

782
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:25,512
AND SAVE EVERYBODY
THE TROUBLE?

783
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:28,139
HERE.

784
00:54:28,139 --> 00:54:31,726
ARE YOU GONNA WORK
WITH ME OR NOT?

785
00:54:34,479 --> 00:54:37,190
( sighs )

786
00:54:37,190 --> 00:54:39,651
<i>ALL RIGHT.</i>

787
00:54:39,651 --> 00:54:41,653
THANKS, MAN.

788
00:54:41,653 --> 00:54:44,447
<i>( phone ringing )</i>

789
00:54:47,659 --> 00:54:48,952
HELLO.

790
00:54:48,952 --> 00:54:51,037
WHERE WERE YOU
LAST NIGHT?

791
00:54:51,037 --> 00:54:53,123
COME ON,

792
00:54:53,123 --> 00:54:55,959
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
START THAT AGAIN,
ARE YOU?

793
00:54:59,462 --> 00:55:02,549
YOU KNOW, JOE'S GOONS
TOOK A SHOT AT ME.

794
00:55:02,549 --> 00:55:03,967
WHAT?

795
00:55:03,967 --> 00:55:06,845
MICHAEL, I'M NOT
WORRIED ABOUT ME.

796
00:55:06,845 --> 00:55:09,806
I'M WORRIED WHAT
THEY'LL DO TO YOU.

797
00:55:17,897 --> 00:55:22,027
EH?
FREAKIN' VIOLETS--

798
00:55:22,027 --> 00:55:24,029
THESE PURPLES ONES
ARE BEAUTIFUL, BEAUTIFUL.

799
00:55:24,029 --> 00:55:26,239
- I WANT SIX FLATS OF THESE.
- SIX OF THOSE.

800
00:55:26,239 --> 00:55:28,616
- YEAH, I WANT THIS COLOR.
- YEAH.

801
00:55:28,616 --> 00:55:31,578
AND THIS TOO.
GO RING THEM UP, EH?

802
00:55:31,578 --> 00:55:33,705
OKAY, I'LL COME BACK
FOR THE REST LATER.

803
00:55:45,091 --> 00:55:48,136
( dings )

804
00:56:57,288 --> 00:56:59,582
( groaning )

805
00:57:28,403 --> 00:57:30,905
<i>( sirens wailing )</i>

806
00:57:42,041 --> 00:57:46,212
JOE, JOE, MAN,
I GOT ONE WORD FOR YOU--
ARIZONA.

807
00:57:46,212 --> 00:57:48,673
<i>GET HIM INSIDE.</i>

808
00:57:48,673 --> 00:57:50,800
EASY, EASY.

809
00:57:54,095 --> 00:57:56,389
AND THEY DIDN'T SAY
WHO THEY WERE FROM?

810
00:57:56,389 --> 00:57:58,391
Man:
NO, MA'AM.

811
00:57:58,391 --> 00:58:00,477
THANK YOU.

812
01:00:26,956 --> 01:00:28,750
HEY.

813
01:00:28,750 --> 01:00:30,752
HMM?

814
01:00:30,752 --> 01:00:34,589
WHY DON'T WE
GO AWAY SOMEWHERE,

815
01:00:34,589 --> 01:00:38,259
GET AWAY
FROM ALL THIS,

816
01:00:38,259 --> 01:00:41,471
START AGAIN TOGETHER,

817
01:00:41,471 --> 01:00:44,349
START CLEAN?

818
01:00:44,349 --> 01:00:46,351
AND I'M GONNA WEAR
A BIG T-SHIRT

819
01:00:46,351 --> 01:00:50,647
SAYING
"JACK THE FUCK-UP."

820
01:00:50,647 --> 01:00:53,566
HAVE YOU EVER BEEN
TO MEXICO?

821
01:00:53,566 --> 01:00:56,069
NO.

822
01:00:56,069 --> 01:00:59,656
WE COULD FLY
INTO OAXACA,

823
01:00:59,656 --> 01:01:01,658
SPEND A FEW WEEKS
ON A BEACH

824
01:01:01,658 --> 01:01:04,410
AT ESCONDIDO,

825
01:01:04,410 --> 01:01:07,455
BUY A CAR CHEAP,

826
01:01:07,455 --> 01:01:10,583
DRIVE TO YUCATAN,

827
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:14,087
MAYBE TRY COSTA RICA.

828
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:16,964
SOUNDS NICE.

829
01:01:16,964 --> 01:01:20,677
MAYBE IN SOME OTHER
LIFETIME.

830
01:01:20,677 --> 01:01:24,138
SWEETHEART,

831
01:01:24,138 --> 01:01:26,808
WE ONLY HAVE THIS ONE.

832
01:01:40,488 --> 01:01:42,740
- HEY, GEORGE.
- GOOD EVENING, SIR.

833
01:01:42,740 --> 01:01:44,742
- SEE YOU, JOE.
- GOOD NIGHT, SIR.
GOOD NIGHT.

834
01:01:44,742 --> 01:01:47,036
<i>( jazz playing )</i>

835
01:02:10,017 --> 01:02:13,062
LET NOBODY SAY
ME AND VINCENT EVER
FORGOT A FAVOR.

836
01:02:13,062 --> 01:02:15,523
YOU HELPED OUT
WITH THE PAROLE.

837
01:02:15,523 --> 01:02:17,525
WE AIN'T FORGOT.

838
01:02:17,525 --> 01:02:20,278
THAT'S GOOD, TOMMY,
BUT WHO'S EMMA DUCKWORTH?

839
01:02:20,278 --> 01:02:23,781
YOU WAS ASKING AROUND
ABOUT ALMA, RIGHT?

840
01:02:23,781 --> 01:02:27,618
SO THIS EMMA DUCKWORTH'S
HER GRANDMOTHER.

841
01:02:34,333 --> 01:02:36,586
APPRECIATE THAT.

842
01:02:40,089 --> 01:02:42,550
- THANK YOU, DEAR.
- YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

843
01:02:42,550 --> 01:02:45,887
MISS DUCKWORTH,
DO YOU RECOGNIZE
THIS LADY RIGHT HERE?

844
01:02:45,887 --> 01:02:48,598
OH, YES.
THIS IS MARIAN.

845
01:02:48,598 --> 01:02:50,600
YOU KNOW,
WHEN SHE WAS YOUNG

846
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:53,102
SHE HAD A BEAUTIFUL
DOLL COLLECTION

847
01:02:53,102 --> 01:02:55,104
AND SHE COULD PLAY
WITH IT

848
01:02:55,104 --> 01:02:56,981
FOREVER AND EVER.
AND IT WAS REALLY--

849
01:02:56,981 --> 01:02:59,650
EXCUSE ME, EXCUSE ME,
NOW WHAT DID YOU SAY
HER NAME WAS?

850
01:02:59,650 --> 01:03:02,236
MARIAN HAMILTON.

851
01:03:03,780 --> 01:03:06,741
YES, THIS IS MARIAN.

852
01:03:06,741 --> 01:03:08,743
I WAS RIGHT THERE
IN THE CHURCH

853
01:03:08,743 --> 01:03:11,496
THE DAY SHE WAS
CHRISTENED.

854
01:03:11,496 --> 01:03:15,208
WHAT ABOUT
THIS GENTLEMAN HERE?

855
01:03:15,208 --> 01:03:17,376
DO YOU RECOGNIZE
THAT FELLOW?

856
01:03:17,376 --> 01:03:19,545
HMM, YES.

857
01:03:19,545 --> 01:03:21,547
THIS IS FRED HAMILTON--

858
01:03:21,547 --> 01:03:23,758
MARIAN'S FATHER,
VERY INTERESTING.

859
01:03:23,758 --> 01:03:27,637
HE COULD READ
A BOOK THIS THICK
IN A DAY.

860
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:29,263
- PROLIFIC.
- YEAH.

861
01:03:29,263 --> 01:03:31,265
WELL, LET ME ASK YOU
A QUESTION:

862
01:03:31,265 --> 01:03:35,061
IF THIS IS HER DAD,
DID MARIAN SPENT ANY TIME
IN AN ORPHANAGE?

863
01:03:35,061 --> 01:03:37,897
OH, FOR HEAVEN'S SAKES, NO.

864
01:03:37,897 --> 01:03:41,734
BUT SHE SPENT TWO YEARS
IN A HOSPITAL.

865
01:03:41,734 --> 01:03:44,320
WHAT KIND OF HOSPITAL?

866
01:03:46,197 --> 01:03:50,159
AND SHE STILL IS
A BIT UNSTABLE.

867
01:03:50,159 --> 01:03:54,455
POOR MARIAN,
SUCH A LOVELY GIRL.

868
01:03:59,168 --> 01:04:01,671
( playing piano )

869
01:04:52,096 --> 01:04:55,391
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO
REACH YOU ALL DAY SO I COULD
FIND OUT WHAT THE GIRL SAID.

870
01:04:55,391 --> 01:04:58,603
BUT THEY SAID YOU TOOK
A FOUR-HOUR LUNCH. AND NOW
YOU EXPECT ME TO BELIEVE

871
01:04:58,603 --> 01:05:01,606
THAT $150,000 WORTH
OF HIGH-TECH EQUIPMENT
JUST STOPPED WORKING?

872
01:05:01,606 --> 01:05:04,859
YEAH, WELL, THESE THINGS HAPPEN.
IT HAPPENED TO ME AND PHIL
THE OTHER DAY IN THE VAN.

873
01:05:04,859 --> 01:05:07,737
- IT HAPPENED LAST YEAR.
- ( phone rings )

874
01:05:07,737 --> 01:05:11,115
VALENTINE.
YEAH.

875
01:05:11,115 --> 01:05:13,492
SHIT.

876
01:05:13,492 --> 01:05:16,245
<i>( siren wailing )</i>

877
01:05:16,245 --> 01:05:20,082
AS YOU CAN SEE BEHIND ME,
THE POLICE ARE COMBING
THE AREA.

878
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:22,668
<i>THEY'RE STILL WAITING</i>
<i>TO RELEASE THE IDENTITY...</i>

879
01:05:25,171 --> 01:05:27,173
- WHERE IS HE?
- IN THE CAR.

880
01:05:27,173 --> 01:05:29,342
WHAT HAPPENED?

881
01:05:29,342 --> 01:05:33,220
MULTIPLE STAB WOUNDS,
ABOUT A DOZEN,
FOR STARTERS.

882
01:05:37,725 --> 01:05:40,311
( sighs )

883
01:05:40,311 --> 01:05:42,772
YOU SHOULD HAVE CALLED,
MICHAEL.

884
01:05:47,735 --> 01:05:49,737
IT'S A GAMBLE WE TOOK
AND WE LOST.

885
01:05:49,737 --> 01:05:52,239
WHAT?

886
01:05:52,239 --> 01:05:55,743
JOE GOT TO NOCERA
BEFORE WE COULD.

887
01:05:58,704 --> 01:06:01,290
THE BAD NEWS IS,
WITHOUT NOCERA,

888
01:06:01,290 --> 01:06:04,001
THE ONLY GUY LEFT
ON YOUR LIST THAT CAN
CRACK THIS FAMILY OPEN

889
01:06:04,001 --> 01:06:07,505
IS JOE BUDDHA HIMSELF.

890
01:06:07,505 --> 01:06:09,548
THE GOOD NEWS IS--

891
01:06:12,677 --> 01:06:14,178
RECOGNIZE THIS?

892
01:06:18,975 --> 01:06:21,769
<i>IT'S ALMA ANSON'S SCARF,</i>
<i>JACK.</i>

893
01:06:26,857 --> 01:06:30,277
I SURE AM GLAD HER SLIPPERS
BED.

894
01:06:53,009 --> 01:06:55,678
- YOU'RE EARLY.
- ARE YOU COMPLAINING?

895
01:06:55,678 --> 01:06:58,097
- NOPE.
- ALL RIGHT.

896
01:06:58,097 --> 01:07:01,350
KNOCK YOURSELF OUT.

897
01:07:01,350 --> 01:07:04,437
- STAY WARM.
- ALL RIGHT, PARTNER.

898
01:07:04,437 --> 01:07:07,273
<i>( door opens</i>
<i>and closes )</i>

899
01:07:07,273 --> 01:07:09,567
<i>( receding footsteps )</i>

900
01:07:16,699 --> 01:07:18,701
<i>( knocks on door )</i>

901
01:07:18,701 --> 01:07:21,245
<i>( gun clicks )</i>

902
01:07:26,417 --> 01:07:28,961
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

903
01:07:28,961 --> 01:07:31,130
WE NEED TO TALK,
MARIAN.

904
01:07:31,130 --> 01:07:33,299
DON'T EVER
CALL ME THAT.

905
01:07:33,299 --> 01:07:37,178
WELL, OF THESE NICE CATS,
YOU SEE, THE SHORT ONE
MUST BE FOR TONY D.

906
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:40,222
THAT WOULD MAKE THIS ONE
FOR MICHAEL NOCERA.

907
01:07:40,222 --> 01:07:43,142
YOU REALLY DID A JOB
ON THOSE GUYS, HUH?

908
01:07:43,142 --> 01:07:45,144
I DIDN'T NEED TO.

909
01:07:45,144 --> 01:07:48,230
THEY LIVE IN A CRUEL WORLD.
THEY DID IT TO THEMSELVES.

910
01:07:48,230 --> 01:07:50,900
SO YOU KEEP TELLING ME.

911
01:07:53,319 --> 01:07:55,571
WHAT'S THIS FOR?

912
01:07:57,448 --> 01:08:00,743
LOOK, I KNOW YOUR DAD
WAS AN ACCOUNTANT
FOR SEA LARK--

913
01:08:00,743 --> 01:08:02,745
JOE BUDDHA'S LITTLE
GAS SCAM.

914
01:08:02,745 --> 01:08:05,539
SO WHAT DO YOU KNOW
THAT GOT THESE GUYS
TO TURN ON EACH OTHER?

915
01:08:05,539 --> 01:08:08,542
JOE BUDDHA DOESN'T DESERVE
TO LIVE AND BREATHE.

916
01:08:10,503 --> 01:08:13,089
WHAT DID HE DO TO YOU?

917
01:08:15,132 --> 01:08:17,885
HE KILLED MY FATHER.

918
01:08:32,775 --> 01:08:35,361
Alma:
<i>MY DAD WAS AN ACCOUNTANT,</i>

919
01:08:35,361 --> 01:08:38,280
<i>AN HONEST ONE.</i>

920
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:40,574
<i>HE MADE THE MISTAKE</i>
<i>OF TAKING ON</i>

921
01:08:40,574 --> 01:08:43,410
<i>THE SEA LARK BOOKS</i>
<i>FOR JOE BUDDHA,</i>

922
01:08:43,410 --> 01:08:46,997
<i>MICHAEL NOCERA</i>
<i>AND TONY D.</i>

923
01:09:09,186 --> 01:09:11,647
<i>BY THE TIME</i>
<i>MY DAD REALIZED</i>

924
01:09:11,647 --> 01:09:13,649
<i>WHO HIS REAL</i>
<i>BOSSES WERE,</i>

925
01:09:13,649 --> 01:09:15,651
<i>HE WAS IN TOO DEEP.</i>

926
01:09:15,651 --> 01:09:17,778
<i>( gunshot )</i>

927
01:09:24,827 --> 01:09:27,454
YOU NEVER TOLD ANYBODY
WHAT YOU SAW?

928
01:09:27,454 --> 01:09:29,915
OF COURSE I DID.

929
01:09:29,915 --> 01:09:32,334
YOU THINK
THEY BELIEVED ME?

930
01:09:32,334 --> 01:09:34,962
THE COPS SAID
IT WAS SUICIDE.

931
01:09:34,962 --> 01:09:37,548
SOMEBODY GOT PAID OFF.

932
01:09:41,093 --> 01:09:45,097
YOU'VE BEEN CARRYING THIS
FOR 15 YEARS.

933
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:52,313
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
ANYMORE.

934
01:09:52,313 --> 01:09:54,773
DO YOU REALIZE

935
01:09:54,773 --> 01:09:57,234
YOU'RE PROBABLY THE ONLY
LIVING WITNESS

936
01:09:57,234 --> 01:10:01,071
THAT'S EVER SEEN JOE BUDDHA
COMMIT A MURDER HIMSELF?

937
01:10:01,071 --> 01:10:03,949
YOU COULD FORCE HIM
TO TURN STATE'S EVIDENCE.

938
01:10:03,949 --> 01:10:06,076
THIS COULD BE
THE BUST OF THE CENTURY.

939
01:10:06,076 --> 01:10:08,078
THE U.S. ATTORNEY'S OFFICE
COULD HAND DOWN

940
01:10:08,078 --> 01:10:10,080
DOZENS OF INDICTMENTS
RIGHT ACROSS THIS COUNTRY.

941
01:10:10,080 --> 01:10:12,416
JOE BUDDHA'S GONNA WALK?

942
01:10:12,416 --> 01:10:14,919
THAT'S JUSTICE ALL RIGHT.

943
01:10:14,919 --> 01:10:18,422
JOE BUDDHA
IN WITNESS PROTECTION

944
01:10:18,422 --> 01:10:21,300
IS A SMALL PRICE TO PAY
FOR PROSECUTIONS
ON THAT SCALE.

945
01:10:21,300 --> 01:10:23,969
ALMA, YOU WANT TO NAIL
THESE GUYS?

946
01:10:23,969 --> 01:10:26,138
YOU FUCKING REALLY
WANT TO NAIL THEM?

947
01:10:26,138 --> 01:10:28,891
YOU COULD ROLL UP
HIS ENTIRE FAMILY.

948
01:10:28,891 --> 01:10:30,893
WASTING THAT
SON OF A BITCH

949
01:10:30,893 --> 01:10:33,687
WOULD FEEL
A WHOLE LOT BETTER.

950
01:10:33,687 --> 01:10:37,608
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA GET
NEXT TO JOE WITH A GUN,

951
01:10:37,608 --> 01:10:40,486
NOT NOW.

952
01:10:40,486 --> 01:10:42,905
YOU NEED ME
TO GET TO HIM.

953
01:10:42,905 --> 01:10:45,741
I CAN WORK IT OUT SO THAT
I'D BE THERE WITH YOU.

954
01:10:45,741 --> 01:10:47,910
I WOULD BE THERE
TO PROTECT YOU.

955
01:10:47,910 --> 01:10:50,287
LIKE YOU WERE THERE
WITH THAT OTHER WOMAN--

956
01:10:50,287 --> 01:10:53,207
THE ONE
THAT WORE THE WIRE?

957
01:11:05,094 --> 01:11:07,805
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

958
01:11:11,809 --> 01:11:13,894
FORGET I ASKED.

959
01:11:34,164 --> 01:11:35,958
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

960
01:11:39,670 --> 01:11:42,423
<i>( Alma's voice )</i>
<i>Look, it was an incredible</i>
<i>night, okay?</i>

961
01:11:43,799 --> 01:11:46,510
<i>Let's just leave it</i>
<i>at that.</i>

962
01:11:50,431 --> 01:11:52,725
<i>( Jack's voice )</i>
<i>We'll have a lot</i>
<i>of nights like that.</i>

963
01:11:52,725 --> 01:11:55,144
( turns off player )

964
01:11:55,144 --> 01:11:59,189
WHAT'S THE MATTER, JACK?
IT GETS BETTER.

965
01:11:59,189 --> 01:12:01,191
YOU'RE SLEEPING
WITH A KEY SUSPECT

966
01:12:01,191 --> 01:12:04,528
IN THE MOST IMPORTANT
O.C. INVESTIGATION
IN 20 YEARS.

967
01:12:04,528 --> 01:12:07,740
AND WHAT'S WORSE, I THINK
YOU'RE PROTECTING HER.

968
01:12:07,740 --> 01:12:10,200
EVERYONE WHO GETS MIXED UP
WITH THIS WOMAN

969
01:12:10,200 --> 01:12:12,202
ENDS UP ON A SLAB
AT THE MORGUE.

970
01:12:12,202 --> 01:12:13,829
DO YOU WANT
TO BE NEXT?

971
01:12:13,829 --> 01:12:17,958
SALLY, I--

972
01:12:17,958 --> 01:12:21,128
I AM SO CLOSE
TO GETTING SOMETHING.

973
01:12:21,128 --> 01:12:23,672
YOU KNOW, WHAT'S TRAGIC
IS THAT THERE'S A PART OF ME

974
01:12:23,672 --> 01:12:28,427
THAT WANTS
TO BELIEVE YOU.

975
01:12:28,427 --> 01:12:31,180
I'M GONNA
HAVE TO HAVE JENNINGS
TAKE YOU OFF THE CASE.

976
01:12:31,180 --> 01:12:34,350
AND THEN I'M GONNA HAVE
TO CALL I.A.D.

977
01:12:34,350 --> 01:12:36,352
THERE'S GONNA BE
AN INVESTIGATION.

978
01:12:36,352 --> 01:12:38,145
THIS IS A MESS.

979
01:12:38,145 --> 01:12:41,982
LISTEN, I CAN DELIVER
JOE BUDDHA

980
01:12:41,982 --> 01:12:43,984
IN 48 HOURS,

981
01:12:43,984 --> 01:12:45,986
READY TO TURN
STATE'S EVIDENCE.

982
01:12:45,986 --> 01:12:47,988
IMPOSSIBLE.

983
01:12:47,988 --> 01:12:50,657
IF I DON'T DO THIS,

984
01:12:50,657 --> 01:12:52,659
I'LL GIVE YOU MY BADGE
AND MY GUN

985
01:12:52,659 --> 01:12:55,537
WITH PLEASURE.

986
01:13:01,210 --> 01:13:04,671
- HEY, MOTHERFUCKER, YOU GOT
SOME 'SPLAINING TO DO.
- HEY, MAN, FUCK YOU.

987
01:13:04,671 --> 01:13:07,132
YOU GO BEHIND MY BACK
AND GIVE THOSE TAPES TO
SALLY CLAIRE? WHY, PHIL?

988
01:13:07,132 --> 01:13:09,218
I DIDN'T TELL CLAIRE
ANYTHING, ALL RIGHT?

989
01:13:09,218 --> 01:13:11,178
SHE ALREADY KNEW
ABOUT YOU AND ALMA.

990
01:13:11,178 --> 01:13:13,722
IT WAS EITHER
HAND OVER THE TAPES
OR LOSE MY FUCKING JOB.

991
01:13:13,722 --> 01:13:16,266
SO YOU COULDN'T
TELL ME YOURSELF?

992
01:13:16,266 --> 01:13:18,685
LOOK, JACK,

993
01:13:18,685 --> 01:13:21,814
I'M SORRY, MAN,
BUT I NEED THIS JOB,
YOU KNOW?

994
01:13:21,814 --> 01:13:24,608
I GOT A WIFE
THAT DEPENDS ON ME.
COME ON.

995
01:13:24,608 --> 01:13:27,277
I WAS GONNA TELL YOU.

996
01:13:27,277 --> 01:13:30,030
LOOK, YOU'D BETTER
TAKE IT EASY, YOU KNOW?

997
01:13:30,030 --> 01:13:32,783
YOU LOSE IT AGAIN,
THEY'RE NOT JUST GONNA
GIVE YOU YOUR DESK JOB.

998
01:13:32,783 --> 01:13:36,370
THEY'RE GONNA KICK YOU
OFF THE DAMN FORCE.

999
01:13:49,091 --> 01:13:51,093
<i>( knocks on door )</i>

1000
01:13:51,093 --> 01:13:53,387
- YEAH?
<i>IT'S ME.</i>

1001
01:14:00,978 --> 01:14:02,980
OKAY, I'LL DO IT

1002
01:14:02,980 --> 01:14:05,774
YOUR WAY.

1003
01:14:23,417 --> 01:14:25,878
YOU WOULD HAVE LIKED
MY DAD.

1004
01:14:25,878 --> 01:14:28,797
I KNOW I WOULD HAVE.

1005
01:14:30,090 --> 01:14:33,802
DO YOU KNOW HOW BLUE
THE SKY IS IN MEXICO?

1006
01:14:33,802 --> 01:14:36,221
HUH-UH.
HOW BLUE?

1007
01:14:36,221 --> 01:14:39,933
IT IS BLUE LIKE
YOU HAVE NEVER SEEN.

1008
01:14:39,933 --> 01:14:43,479
AND I KNOW A PLACE
WHERE THE SAND ISN'T WHITE,

1009
01:14:43,479 --> 01:14:45,481
IT'S PINK.

1010
01:14:45,481 --> 01:14:47,900
PINK SAND?

1011
01:14:47,900 --> 01:14:50,027
I LIKE THAT.

1012
01:15:00,204 --> 01:15:03,707
Tommy:
<i>...A MINIATURE STEINWAY,</i>
<i>RIGHT?</i>

1013
01:15:03,707 --> 01:15:06,043
AND THE GENIE SAYS,

1014
01:15:06,043 --> 01:15:08,462
"I'M SORRY, LADY.
I THOUGHT YOU MEANT

1015
01:15:08,462 --> 01:15:11,757
A 9" PIANIST."

1016
01:15:11,757 --> 01:15:13,509
CUTE.

1017
01:15:13,509 --> 01:15:15,260
TOMMY, LET ME SEE YOU.
COME HERE.

1018
01:15:15,260 --> 01:15:16,887
HEY, JACK,
HOW IS IT GOING?

1019
01:15:16,887 --> 01:15:18,514
GOOD. LET ME
SEE YOU, PLEASE.

1020
01:15:18,514 --> 01:15:20,933
EXCUSE ME, GENTLEMEN.
SURE. WHAT'S HAPPENING?

1021
01:15:20,933 --> 01:15:23,519
LISTEN, I NEED TO GET
A WORD WITH JOEY B.

1022
01:15:23,519 --> 01:15:25,521
CAN YOU HOOK THAT UP
FOR ME?

1023
01:15:25,521 --> 01:15:29,066
JESUS, JACK, FUCK.
I'M GRATEFUL AND
EVERYTHING,

1024
01:15:29,066 --> 01:15:31,568
BUT YOU'RE PUTTING ME
ON THE FUCKING SPOT HERE.

1025
01:15:31,568 --> 01:15:33,570
TOMMY, ONE LITTLE
CONVERSATION.

1026
01:15:33,570 --> 01:15:35,572
PLEASE SIT DOWN.
SIT DOWN.

1027
01:15:35,572 --> 01:15:38,867
ONE LITTLE CONVERSATION,
THAT'S ALL I NEED.
AND YOU CAN DO THAT.

1028
01:15:41,036 --> 01:15:43,789
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND,
DETECTIVE.

1029
01:15:43,789 --> 01:15:47,459
TWO BIG GUYS ARE DEAD.
NOBODY KNOWS WHERE
JOE IS EVEN.

1030
01:15:47,459 --> 01:15:49,044
ARE YOU SAYING
HE'S SCARED?

1031
01:15:49,044 --> 01:15:52,047
JOE? HE AIN'T BEEN SCARED
IN 30 YEARS.

1032
01:15:52,047 --> 01:15:55,509
HE'S WHAT YOU MIGHT CALL
CONCERNED, ALL RIGHT, BUT--

1033
01:15:55,509 --> 01:15:58,011
I'M CONCERNED.
EVERYBODY'S CONCERNED.

1034
01:15:58,011 --> 01:16:01,723
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET
THE MAN SOME USEFUL
INFORMATION.

1035
01:16:01,723 --> 01:16:03,725
OFFICIAL OR UNOFFICIAL?

1036
01:16:03,725 --> 01:16:05,394
<i>I WANT TO HAVE DINNER</i>
<i>WITH THE GUY,</i>

1037
01:16:05,394 --> 01:16:07,396
COMPLETELY OFF THE RECORD.

1038
01:16:07,396 --> 01:16:09,106
CAN YOU SET THAT UP?

1039
01:16:22,995 --> 01:16:25,998
I CAN'T BELIEVE
KEENAN AGREED TO THIS.

1040
01:16:25,998 --> 01:16:28,750
WELL, HE DIDN'T
ACTUALLY AGREE.

1041
01:16:30,877 --> 01:16:32,879
WHAT, YOU MEAN
HE DOESN'T KNOW?

1042
01:16:32,879 --> 01:16:34,881
NO, NOT EXACTLY.

1043
01:16:34,881 --> 01:16:37,384
WAIT, WAIT, WHAT THE FUCK
DO YOU MEAN, NOT EXACTLY?

1044
01:16:37,384 --> 01:16:40,262
KEENAN FINDS OUT THAT
WE'RE RUNNING OUR OWN
PERSONAL BLACK OPS HERE,

1045
01:16:40,262 --> 01:16:42,681
HE'S GONNA SHITCAN
THE BOTH OF US,
GOD DAMN IT.

1046
01:16:42,681 --> 01:16:45,601
PHIL, PHIL, LOOK,
JUST WORK WITH ME
ON THIS ONE, OKAY?

1047
01:16:45,601 --> 01:16:48,020
NOW YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT PIMPED ME ON THE TAPES
TO SALLY CLAIRE.

1048
01:16:48,020 --> 01:16:51,398
I PIMPED YOU?
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT GOT
INVOLVED WITH A WITNESS, JACK.

1049
01:16:51,398 --> 01:16:53,400
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT'S GOT HER
WEARING THE WIRE.

1050
01:16:53,400 --> 01:16:55,444
DOES THIS SOUND
FAMILIAR?

1051
01:16:55,444 --> 01:16:57,613
PHIL, ALL YOU GOTTA DO
IS SIT IN THIS LITTLE VAN,

1052
01:16:57,613 --> 01:17:00,991
PRESS "RECORD"
AND HOPE THIS SHIT WORKS.
CAN YOU PLEASE DO THAT?

1053
01:17:06,079 --> 01:17:08,081
HOW IS THIS GIRL

1054
01:17:08,081 --> 01:17:10,584
GONNA GET JOE B
TO TURN ANYWAY?

1055
01:17:10,584 --> 01:17:12,669
LET ME WORRY
ABOUT THAT, OKAY?

1056
01:17:16,882 --> 01:17:19,343
GET THE FUCK
OUT OF HERE.

1057
01:17:24,181 --> 01:17:28,185
OH, JESUS CHRIST.

1058
01:17:28,185 --> 01:17:30,520
DETECTIVE, MY PEOPLE
TELL ME

1059
01:17:30,520 --> 01:17:32,773
YOU'RE A VERY
COMPASSIONATE GUY,

1060
01:17:32,773 --> 01:17:37,277
AN ODDBALL,
BUT VERY KIND INDIVIDUAL.
AND I LIKE THAT.

1061
01:17:37,277 --> 01:17:39,279
WELL, I APPRECIATE
THAT, JOE.

1062
01:17:39,279 --> 01:17:41,281
OF COURSE
YOU'RE COMPASSIONATE

1063
01:17:41,281 --> 01:17:44,576
SO FUCKING MOPES TAKE YOU
INTO THEIR CONFIDENCE.
( chuckling )

1064
01:17:44,576 --> 01:17:46,578
AND THAT'S VERY IMPORTANT
IN YOUR LINE OF WORK.

1065
01:17:46,578 --> 01:17:48,789
WELL, PEOPLE SKILLS
CAN BE HELPFUL, YES.

1066
01:17:48,789 --> 01:17:51,458
<i>( knocks on door )</i>
<i>( door opens )</i>

1067
01:17:53,251 --> 01:17:56,755
WHAT'S THIS, DETECTIVE?
I THOUGHT WE WERE GONNA
DINE ALONE.

1068
01:17:56,755 --> 01:17:58,715
<i>Well, Alma here</i>
<i>is a friend of mine.</i>

1069
01:17:58,715 --> 01:18:00,509
<i>She's been dying</i>
<i>to meet you.</i>

1070
01:18:00,509 --> 01:18:02,511
<i>And I think you're gonna</i>
<i>want to hear her out.</i>

1071
01:18:02,511 --> 01:18:04,513
<i>Sit down, sweetheart.</i>

1072
01:18:04,513 --> 01:18:06,848
<i>Now Tommy said you had</i>
<i>some information for me?</i>

1073
01:18:06,848 --> 01:18:11,019
<i>Well, actually</i>
<i>Alma's the one</i>
<i>with the information.</i>

1074
01:18:11,019 --> 01:18:14,064
SO WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

1075
01:18:14,064 --> 01:18:18,527
I HELPED MICHAEL NOCERA
KILL YOUR PAL TONY D.

1076
01:18:21,947 --> 01:18:25,492
<i>I TOLD MICHAEL</i>
<i>THAT YOU AND TONY</i>
<i>WERE SKIMMING HIM</i>

1077
01:18:25,492 --> 01:18:27,994
